    <h3>BC/BN Series: Standout Features</h3>
    <p>The reversing fan motor is the feature that most distinguishes Sinmag convection ovens from cheaper Indian alternatives. In a standard single-direction fan convection oven, the tray closest to the fan always gets slightly more airflow and browns faster. The reversing fan eliminates this, meaning tray 1 and tray 8 in a BC-808 bake almost identically. For high-volume operations where consistency matters commercially, this is important.</p>
    <p>The BN series adds a programmable recipe memory (up to 99 programmes on the BN-810/816), which is useful for multi-product bakeries where different items need different time/temperature combinations. The enhanced insulation on the BN series also results in better energy efficiency — Sinmag claims approximately 15% lower energy consumption vs the BC series. In a high-use environment, that difference adds up.</p>
    <p>Steam on the convection ovens is available as an option on floor models (BC-808 and above) — it's a simple water injection system rather than the boiler-based steam of the deck ovens, but adequate for croissants, baguettes, and similar products.</p>

