    <h2>3. Sinmag Rotary Rack Ovens (ER Series): Full Review</h2>
    <p>Sinmag's rotary rack ovens are positioned at the high-volume end of the market. The ER series covers half-rack and full-rack configurations, available in gas and electric. These are serious industrial machines — the full-rack ER-26 handles a full rack of 18–24 trays in a single cycle, making it suitable for bakeries producing thousands of pieces per shift.</p>
    <p>The rotary mechanism in the ER series is a proven pendulum-swing design that rotates the rack on both horizontal and vertical axes, ensuring every tray gets equal heat exposure. Sinmag has invested in burner technology for the gas-fired models that achieves low NOx emissions — relevant if your bakery is in an area with strict emissions regulations.</p>

