    <h3>ER Series: Who Should Buy This?</h3>
    <p>The ER rotary ovens make economic sense when you're producing over 800–1,000 pieces per hour consistently. Below that volume, a 3-deck or 4-deck oven will cost less to purchase and has lower energy overhead. The sweet spot for rotary ovens is industrial bakeries, hotel central kitchens, large QSR chains, and institutional catering operations.</p>
    <p>One practical consideration for Indian buyers: the full-rack ER-26 and ER-32 require a minimum ceiling height of 3.2 metres. Many older commercial buildings in India fall short of this. Always measure your ceiling clearance before ordering.</p>

