    <h3>Summary: Where Sinmag Wins and Where It Falls Short</h3>
    <p><strong>Sinmag wins on:</strong> Value for money (consistently 25–40% cheaper than comparable European models), service network quality in India (better than Bongard, comparable to Unox), product reliability (very low reported failure rates among Indian users), steam injection quality on deck ovens (significantly better than Indian brands), and tray format compatibility (60×40 standard trays throughout).</p>
    <p><strong>Sinmag falls short on:</strong> Connectivity and smart features (Unox's BAKERTOP intelligence is in a different league for programmability), absolute peak baking quality for specialist artisan bread (Bongard's steam and stone quality is marginally superior), and energy efficiency at the top end (European brands have invested more in insulation and burner technology).</p>
    <p><strong>The verdict:</strong> For Indian bakeries, Sinmag hits a sweet spot that no other brand currently occupies — better than Indian brands in every meaningful way, but priced well below equivalent European alternatives. For 80% of Indian bakery operations, Sinmag is probably the right choice on a quality-vs-cost basis.</p>

