    <h2>Where to Buy Sinmag Ovens in India</h2>
    <p>Sinmag does not sell directly to end users in India. All sales go through authorised importers and distributors. The key thing to understand is the two-tier distribution structure in India: national importers who hold stock and handle warranty, and regional dealers who sell on their behalf. Buying from the national importer directly usually saves you the dealer's margin.</p>

    <h3>What to Ask When Buying Sinmag in India</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Is this an authorised importer or a grey-market unit?</strong> Grey market Sinmag units (imported without authorisation) do exist in India. They're typically 10–15% cheaper but come with no warranty and no official service support. Ask for the importer's authorisation documentation.</li>
      <li><strong>What is the warranty, and who backs it?</strong> Get the warranty terms in writing — particularly who covers labour costs for repairs within the warranty period. Some distributors cover parts only, not labour.</li>
      <li><strong>Is it Taiwan-made or China-made?</strong> Sinmag manufactures some models in their Chinese facility (typically entry/mid range) and premium models in Taiwan. Ask specifically. Taiwan-made units have a slight quality edge.</li>
      <li><strong>What is the lead time?</strong> Popular models are often in stock in Delhi or Mumbai warehouses. Less common models may need to be ordered from Taiwan — allow 6–10 weeks.</li>
      <li><strong>Installation included?</strong> For deck ovens and rotary rack ovens, professional installation is important. Confirm whether it's included in the price or billed separately.</li>
    </ul>

